# Cursor Glass alignment

[Cursor Glass](https://cursor.com/glass) emphasizes **clarity**, **intuitive structure**, and **user control** when working with agents.

## For this repository

- **README and docs** lead with **outcomes**, then link to detail. Keep an **executive summary** at the top of the README.
- **No chain-of-thought** in user-facing markdown: write for a human reader.
- Prefer **short sections** and **scannable headings** in `docs/` and the GitHub Pages showcase.
- Use the **Agent Window** (Cursor 3+) for multi-step tasks; break work into reviewable slices when changes are risky.

## GitHub Pages

Keep `docs/index.html` lightweight: purpose, links to guides, examples—no internal planning artifacts.
